{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"So when I was a kid ..."},{"time":3080,"text":"this was my team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5600,"text":"I stunk at sports."},{"time":7640,"text":"I didn't like to play them,\nI didn't like to watch them."},{"time":10880,"text":"So this is what I did. I went fishing."},{"time":13160,"text":"And for all of my growing up\nI fished on the shores of Connecticut,"},{"time":16680,"text":"and these are the creatures\nthat I saw on a regular basis."},{"time":20600,"text":"But after I grew up and went to college,"},{"time":23240,"text":"and I came home in the early 90's,"},{"time":25920,"text":"this is what I found."},{"time":27640,"text":"My team had shrunk."},{"time":29280,"text":"It was like literally having\nyour roster devastated."},{"time":32400,"text":"And as I sort of looked into that,"},{"time":34440,"text":"from a very personal\npoint of view as a fisherman,"},{"time":36840,"text":"I started to kind of figure out,"},{"time":38440,"text":"well, what was the rest of the world\nthinking about it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41040,"text":"First place I started to look\nwas fish markets."},{"time":43280,"text":"And when I went to fish markets,"},{"time":45080,"text":"in spite of where I was --"},{"time":46360,"text":"whether I was in North Carolina,\nor Paris, or London, or wherever --"},{"time":50440,"text":"I kept seeing this weirdly\nrepeating trope of four creatures,"},{"time":55640,"text":"again and again --"},{"time":56880,"text":"on the menus, on ice --"},{"time":58480,"text":"shrimp, tuna, salmon and cod."},{"time":61360,"text":"And I thought this was pretty strange,"},{"time":63760,"text":"and as I looked at it, I was wondering,"},{"time":65800,"text":"did anyone else notice\nthis sort of shrinking of the market?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":69440,"text":"Well, when I looked into it,"},{"time":70840,"text":"I realized that people\ndidn't look at it as their team."},{"time":73760,"text":"Ordinary people, the way they looked\nat seafood was like this."},{"time":77440,"text":"It's not an unusual human characteristic"},{"time":79920,"text":"to reduce the natural world\ndown to very few elements."},{"time":83640,"text":"We did it before, 10,000 years ago,\nwhen we came out of our caves."},{"time":86960,"text":"If you look at fire pits\nfrom 10,000 years ago,"},{"time":89520,"text":"you'll see raccoons,\nyou'll see, you know, wolves,"},{"time":92120,"text":"you'll see all kinds\nof different creatures."},{"time":94200,"text":"But if you telescope to the age of --\nyou know, 2,000 years ago,"},{"time":97880,"text":"you'll see these four mammals:"},{"time":99800,"text":"pigs, cows, sheep and goats."},{"time":102240,"text":"It's true of birds, too."},{"time":103480,"text":"You look at the menus\nin New York City restaurants"},{"time":106320,"text":"150 years ago, 200 years ago,"},{"time":108240,"text":"you'll see snipe, woodcock, grouse,\ndozens of ducks, dozens of geese."},{"time":113000,"text":"But telescope ahead to the age\nof modern animal husbandry,"},{"time":115960,"text":"and you'll see four:"},{"time":117360,"text":"turkeys, ducks, chicken and geese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120480,"text":"So it makes sense\nthat we've headed in this direction."},{"time":123080,"text":"But how have we headed in this direction?"},{"time":125057,"text":"Well ..."},{"time":126280,"text":"first it's a very, very new problem."},{"time":128160,"text":"This is the way we've been fishing\nthe oceans over the last 50 years."},{"time":131920,"text":"World War II was a tremendous incentive\nto arm ourselves in a war against fish."},{"time":137160,"text":"All of the technology\nthat we perfected during World War II --"},{"time":140440,"text":"sonar, lightweight polymers --"},{"time":142120,"text":"all these things\nwere redirected towards fish."},{"time":144440,"text":"And so you see this tremendous buildup\nin fishing capacity,"},{"time":147880,"text":"quadrupling in the course of time,"},{"time":149560,"text":"from the end of World War II\nto the present time."},{"time":152480,"text":"And right now that means"},{"time":153880,"text":"we're taking between 80 and 90 million\nmetric tons out of the sea every year."},{"time":157560,"text":"That's the equivalent\nof the human weight of China"},{"time":160800,"text":"taken out of the sea every year."},{"time":162360,"text":"And it's no coincidence\nthat I use China as the example"},{"time":165000,"text":"because China is now\nthe largest fishing nation in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168040,"text":"Well, that's only half the story."},{"time":169680,"text":"The other half of the story"},{"time":171080,"text":"is this incredible boom\nin fish farming and aquaculture,"},{"time":175160,"text":"which is now, only\nin the last year or two,"},{"time":177400,"text":"starting to exceed the amount\nof wild fish that we produce."},{"time":180800,"text":"So that if you add wild fish\nand farmed fish together,"},{"time":184840,"text":"you get the equivalent\nof two Chinas created from the ocean"},{"time":188320,"text":"each and every year."},{"time":189600,"text":"And again, it's not a coincidence\nthat I use China as the example,"},{"time":192760,"text":"because China, in addition\nto being the biggest catcher of fish,"},{"time":195840,"text":"is also the biggest farmer of fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198840,"text":"So let's look though at the four choices\nwe are making right now."},{"time":203400,"text":"The first one --"},{"time":204640,"text":"by far the most consumed seafood\nin America and in much of the West,"},{"time":208360,"text":"is shrimp."},{"time":209600,"text":"Shrimp in the wild --\nas a wild product --"},{"time":212080,"text":"is a terrible product."},{"time":213440,"text":"5, 10, 15 pounds of wild fish\nare regularly killed"},{"time":217920,"text":"to bring one pound of shrimp\nto the market."},{"time":220360,"text":"They're also incredibly fuel inefficient\nto bring to the market."},{"time":223480,"text":"In a recent study that was produced\nout of Dalhousie University,"},{"time":226600,"text":"it was found that dragging for shrimp"},{"time":228440,"text":"is one of the most carbon-intensive\nways of fishing that you can find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232640,"text":"So you can farm them,"},{"time":234320,"text":"and people do farm them,"},{"time":235600,"text":"and they farm them a lot\nin this very area."},{"time":237640,"text":"Problem is ..."},{"time":238880,"text":"the place where you farm shrimp\nis in these wild habitats --"},{"time":242120,"text":"in mangrove forests."},{"time":243360,"text":"Now look at those lovely\nroots coming down."},{"time":245440,"text":"Those are the things\nthat hold soil together,"},{"time":247560,"text":"protect coasts, create habitats\nfor all sorts of young fish, young shrimp,"},{"time":251360,"text":"all sorts of things\nthat are important to this environment."},{"time":254161,"text":"Well, this is what happens\nto a lot of coastal mangrove forests."},{"time":257185,"text":"We've lost millions of acres\nof coastal mangroves"},{"time":259519,"text":"over the last 30 or 40 years."},{"time":260959,"text":"That rate of destruction has slowed,"},{"time":263440,"text":"but we're still\nin a major mangrove deficit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266760,"text":"The other thing that's going on here"},{"time":268520,"text":"is a phenomenon that the filmmaker\nMark Benjamin called \"Grinding Nemo.\""},{"time":272680,"text":"This phenomenon is very, very relevant"},{"time":275200,"text":"to anything that you've ever seen\non a tropical reef."},{"time":277720,"text":"Because what's going on right now,"},{"time":279400,"text":"we have shrimp draggers\ndragging for shrimp,"},{"time":281600,"text":"catching a huge amount of bycatch,"},{"time":283480,"text":"that bycatch in turn gets ground up\nand turned into shrimp food."},{"time":287600,"text":"And sometimes, many of these vessels --"},{"time":289760,"text":"manned by slaves --"},{"time":291160,"text":"are catching these so-called \"trash fish,\""},{"time":293880,"text":"fish that we would love to see on a reef,"},{"time":295857,"text":"grinding them up"},{"time":297080,"text":"and turning them into shrimp feed --"},{"time":298864,"text":"an ecosystem literally eating itself\nand spitting out shrimp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303120,"text":"The next most consumed seafood in America,"},{"time":305320,"text":"and also throughout the West,"},{"time":307040,"text":"is tuna."},{"time":308280,"text":"So tuna is this ultimate global fish."},{"time":311360,"text":"These huge management areas\nhave to be observed"},{"time":314400,"text":"in order for tuna to be well managed."},{"time":316360,"text":"Our own management area,"},{"time":318160,"text":"called a Regional Fisheries\nManagement Organization,"},{"time":320640,"text":"is called ICCAT,"},{"time":321880,"text":"the International Commission\nfor the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas."},{"time":325120,"text":"The great naturalist\nCarl Safina once called it,"},{"time":327840,"text":"\"The International Conspiracy\nto Catch all the Tunas.\""},{"time":331120,"text":"Of course we've seen\nincredible improvement"},{"time":333200,"text":"in ICCAT in the last few years,"},{"time":334720,"text":"there is total room for improvement,"},{"time":336480,"text":"but it remains to be said\nthat tuna is a global fish,"},{"time":339400,"text":"and to manage it,\nwe have to manage the globe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342240,"text":"Well, we could also try to grow tuna"},{"time":344200,"text":"but tuna is a spectacularly bad\nanimal for aquaculture."},{"time":347840,"text":"Many people don't know this\nbut tuna are warm-blooded."},{"time":350960,"text":"They can heat their bodies 20 degrees\nabove ambient temperature,"},{"time":354400,"text":"they can swim at over 40 miles an hour."},{"time":356520,"text":"So that pretty much eliminates"},{"time":358280,"text":"all the advantages\nof farming a fish, right?"},{"time":360400,"text":"A farmed fish is --"},{"time":361640,"text":"or a fish is cold-blooded,\nit doesn't move too much."},{"time":364093,"text":"That's a great thing for growing protein."},{"time":366120,"text":"But if you've got\nthis crazy, wild creature"},{"time":368480,"text":"that swims at 40 miles an hour\nand heats its blood --"},{"time":371000,"text":"not a great candidate for aquaculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373760,"text":"The next creature --"},{"time":375000,"text":"most consumed seafood in America\nand throughout the West --"},{"time":378000,"text":"is salmon."},{"time":379240,"text":"Now salmon got its plundering, too,"},{"time":381440,"text":"but it didn't really necessarily\nhappen through fishing."},{"time":384600,"text":"This is my home state of Connecticut."},{"time":386400,"text":"Connecticut used to be home\nto a lot of wild salmon."},{"time":389480,"text":"But if you look\nat this map of Connecticut,"},{"time":391560,"text":"every dot on that map is a dam."},{"time":395400,"text":"There are over 3,000 dams\nin the state of Connecticut."},{"time":399280,"text":"I often say this is why people\nin Connecticut are so uptight --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404440,"text":"If somebody could just\nunblock Connecticut's chi,"},{"time":408000,"text":"I feel that we could have\nan infinitely better world."},{"time":410520,"text":"But I made this particular comment"},{"time":412280,"text":"at a convention once\nof national parks officers,"},{"time":414960,"text":"and this guy from North Carolina\nsidled up to me, he says,"},{"time":417720,"text":"\"You know, you oughtn't be so hard\non your Connecticut,"},{"time":421040,"text":"cause we here in North Carolina,\nwe got 35,000 dams.\""},{"time":425880,"text":"So it's a national epidemic,\nit's an international epidemic."},{"time":428760,"text":"And there are dams everywhere,"},{"time":430240,"text":"and these are precisely the things"},{"time":431920,"text":"that stop wild salmon\nfrom reaching their spawning grounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434720,"text":"So as a result,\nwe've turned to aquaculture,"},{"time":436840,"text":"and salmon is one the most successful,\nat least from a numbers point of view."},{"time":440520,"text":"When they first started farming salmon,"},{"time":442760,"text":"it could take as many\nas six pounds of wild fish"},{"time":445720,"text":"to make a single pound of salmon."},{"time":447920,"text":"The industry has, to its credit,\ngreatly improved."},{"time":450600,"text":"They've gotten it below two to one,"},{"time":452291,"text":"although it's a little bit of a cheat"},{"time":454600,"text":"because if you look at the way\naquaculture feed is produced,"},{"time":457440,"text":"they're measuring pellets --"},{"time":458920,"text":"pounds of pellets per pound of salmon."},{"time":461200,"text":"Those pellets are in turn reduced fish."},{"time":463880,"text":"So the actual -- what's called the FIFO,\nthe fish in and the fish out --"},{"time":467400,"text":"kind of hard to say."},{"time":468760,"text":"But in any case,"},{"time":470000,"text":"credit to the industry,"},{"time":471240,"text":"it has lowered the amount of fish\nper pound of salmon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473840,"text":"Problem is we've also gone crazy"},{"time":476040,"text":"with the amount of salmon\nthat we're producing."},{"time":478280,"text":"Aquaculture is the fastest growing\nfood system on the planet."},{"time":481920,"text":"It's growing at something\nlike seven percent per year."},{"time":484920,"text":"And so even though\nwe're doing less per fish"},{"time":488960,"text":"to bring it to the market,"},{"time":490280,"text":"we're still killing\na lot of these little fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493040,"text":"And it's not just fish\nthat we're feeding fish to,"},{"time":496240,"text":"we're also feeding fish\nto chickens and pigs."},{"time":499600,"text":"So we've got chickens\nand they're eating fish,"},{"time":502560,"text":"but weirdly, we also have fish\nthat are eating chickens."},{"time":506840,"text":"Because the byproducts of chickens --\nfeathers, blood, bone --"},{"time":509960,"text":"get ground up and fed to fish."},{"time":512280,"text":"So I often wonder,"},{"time":513520,"text":"is there a fish that ate\na chicken that ate a fish?"},{"time":517360,"text":"It's sort of a reworking\nof the chicken and egg thing. Anyway --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521520,"text":"All together, though,\nit results in a terrible mess."},{"time":524320,"text":"What you're talking about"},{"time":525720,"text":"is something between 20 and 30 million\nmetric tons of wild creatures"},{"time":531400,"text":"that are taken from the ocean\nand used and ground up."},{"time":534400,"text":"That's the equivalent\nof a third of a China,"},{"time":536480,"text":"or of an entire United States of humans"},{"time":538560,"text":"that's taken out of the sea\neach and every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542160,"text":"The last of the four\nis a kind of amorphous thing."},{"time":544720,"text":"It's what the industry calls \"whitefish.\""},{"time":548240,"text":"There are many fish that get cycled\ninto this whitefish thing"},{"time":551240,"text":"but the way to kind of tell\nthe story, I think,"},{"time":553480,"text":"is through that classic piece\nof American culinary innovation,"},{"time":556440,"text":"the Filet-O-Fish sandwich."},{"time":557840,"text":"So the Filet-O-Fish sandwich\nactually started as halibut."},{"time":560840,"text":"And it started because\na local franchise owner"},{"time":563200,"text":"found that when he served\nhis McDonald's on Friday, nobody came."},{"time":568760,"text":"Because it was a Catholic\ncommunity, they needed fish."},{"time":571320,"text":"So he went to Ray Kroc and he said,"},{"time":573200,"text":"\"I'm going to bring you a fish sandwich,\ngoing to be made out of halibut.\""},{"time":576720,"text":"Ray Kroc said, \"I don't think\nit's going to work."},{"time":579040,"text":"I want to do a Hula Burger,"},{"time":580360,"text":"and there's going to be\na slice of pineapple on a bun."},{"time":582908,"text":"But let's do this, let's have a bet."},{"time":584668,"text":"Whosever sandwich sells more,\nthat will be the winning sandwich.\""},{"time":588200,"text":"Well, it's kind of sad for the ocean\nthat the Hula Burger didn't win."},{"time":592560,"text":"So he made his halibut sandwich."},{"time":594720,"text":"Unfortunately though,\nthe sandwich came in at 30 cents."},{"time":598080,"text":"Ray wanted the sandwich\nto come in at 25 cents,"},{"time":600640,"text":"so he turned to Atlantic cod."},{"time":602600,"text":"We all know what happened to\nAtlantic cod in New England."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605400,"text":"So now the Filet-O-Fish sandwich\nis made out of Alaska pollock,"},{"time":608920,"text":"it's the largest fin fish fishery\nin the United States,"},{"time":611680,"text":"2 to 3 billion pounds of fish\ntaken out of the sea every single year."},{"time":616080,"text":"If we go through the pollock,"},{"time":617640,"text":"the next choice is probably\ngoing to be tilapia."},{"time":620120,"text":"Tilapia is one of those fish\nnobody ever heard of 20 years ago."},{"time":623120,"text":"It's actually a very efficient converter\nof plant protein into animal protein,"},{"time":627400,"text":"and it's been a godsend\nto the third world."},{"time":629480,"text":"It's actually a tremendously\nsustainable solution,"},{"time":631880,"text":"it goes from an egg\nto an adult in nine months."},{"time":634120,"text":"The problem is that when you\nlook about the West,"},{"time":636480,"text":"it doesn't do what the West\nwants it to do."},{"time":638520,"text":"It really doesn't have what's called\nan oily fish profile."},{"time":641280,"text":"It doesn't have the EPA and DHA omega-3s"},{"time":643680,"text":"that we all think are going\nto make us live forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":648520,"text":"I mean, first of all,\nwhat about this poor fish, the clupeids?"},{"time":651720,"text":"The fish that represent a huge part\nof that 20 to 30 million metric tons."},{"time":656760,"text":"Well, one possibility\nthat a lot of conservationists have raised"},{"time":659840,"text":"is could we eat them?"},{"time":661480,"text":"Could we eat them directly\ninstead of feeding them to salmon?"},{"time":664400,"text":"There are arguments for it."},{"time":665760,"text":"They are tremendously fuel efficient\nto bring to market,"},{"time":668404,"text":"a fraction of the fuel cost\nof say, shrimp,"},{"time":670520,"text":"and at the very top\nof the carbon efficiency scale."},{"time":673880,"text":"They also are omega-3 rich,\na great source for EPA and DHA."},{"time":678040,"text":"So that is a potential."},{"time":679520,"text":"And if we were to go down that route\nwhat I would say is,"},{"time":683240,"text":"instead of paying a few bucks a pound --\nor a few bucks a ton, really --"},{"time":687080,"text":"and making it into aquafeed,"},{"time":689080,"text":"could we halve the catch\nand double the price for the fishermen"},{"time":692400,"text":"and make that our way\nof treating these particular fish?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":697200,"text":"Other possibility though,\nwhich is much more interesting,"},{"time":699920,"text":"is looking at bivalves,\nparticularly mussels."},{"time":702320,"text":"Now, mussels are very high in EPA and DHA,\nthey're similar to canned tuna."},{"time":707280,"text":"They're also extremely fuel efficient."},{"time":709240,"text":"To bring a pound of mussels to market"},{"time":711080,"text":"is about a thirtieth of the carbon\nas required to bring beef to market."},{"time":714720,"text":"They require no forage fish,"},{"time":716320,"text":"they actually get their omega-3s\nby filtering the water of microalgae."},{"time":720600,"text":"In fact, that's where omega-3s come from,\nthey don't come from fish."},{"time":723840,"text":"Microalgae make the omega-3s,\nthey're only bioconcentrated in fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727920,"text":"Mussels and other bivalves"},{"time":729200,"text":"do tremendous amounts of water filtration."},{"time":731224,"text":"A single mussel can filter\ndozens of gallons every single day."},{"time":734800,"text":"And this is incredibly important\nwhen we look at the world."},{"time":737600,"text":"Right now, nitrification,\noveruse of phosphates in our waterways"},{"time":741200,"text":"are causing tremendous algal blooms."},{"time":743560,"text":"Over 400 new dead zones\nhave been created in the last 20 years,"},{"time":747840,"text":"tremendous sources of marine life death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752320,"text":"We also could look at not a fish at all."},{"time":754520,"text":"We could look at a vegetable."},{"time":755960,"text":"We could look at seaweed, the kelps,"},{"time":757720,"text":"all these different varieties of things\nthat can be high in omega-3s,"},{"time":761080,"text":"can be high in proteins,"},{"time":762400,"text":"tremendously good things."},{"time":764040,"text":"They filter the water\njust like mussels do."},{"time":766720,"text":"And weirdly enough,"},{"time":768000,"text":"it turns out that you\ncan actually feed this to cows."},{"time":770640,"text":"Now, I'm not a big fan of cattle."},{"time":772880,"text":"But if you wanted to keep growing cattle"},{"time":774840,"text":"in a time and place\nwhere water resources are limited,"},{"time":777680,"text":"you're growing seaweed in the water,\nyou don't have to water it --"},{"time":780800,"text":"major consideration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782480,"text":"And the last fish is a question mark."},{"time":785240,"text":"We have the ability\nto create aquacultured fish"},{"time":789120,"text":"that creates a net gain\nof marine protein for us."},{"time":792560,"text":"This creature would have to be vegetarian,"},{"time":794720,"text":"it would have to be fast growing,"},{"time":796520,"text":"it would have to be adaptable\nto a changing climate"},{"time":799200,"text":"and it would have to have\nthat oily fish profile,"},{"time":801560,"text":"that EPA, DHA, omega-3\nfatty acid profile that we're looking for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805480,"text":"This exists kind of on paper."},{"time":808440,"text":"I have been reporting\non these subjects for 15 years."},{"time":812080,"text":"Every time I do a new story,\nsomebody tells me,"},{"time":815000,"text":"\"We can do all that. We can do it.\nWe've figured it all out."},{"time":817880,"text":"We can produce a fish"},{"time":819120,"text":"that's a net gain of marine protein\nand has omega-3s.\""},{"time":821720,"text":"Great."},{"time":822960,"text":"It doesn't seem to be getting scaled up."},{"time":825120,"text":"It is time to scale this up."},{"time":826880,"text":"If we do,"},{"time":828120,"text":"30 million metric tons of seafood,\na third of the world catch,"},{"time":831640,"text":"stays in the water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833880,"text":"So I guess what I'm saying is\nthis is what we've been going with."},{"time":837200,"text":"We tend to go with our appetites\nrather than our minds."},{"time":840400,"text":"But if we went with this,\nor some configuration of it,"},{"time":843920,"text":"we might have a little more of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847120,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848360,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}